    <ol style=3D"margin-left:-1rem;" start=3D"2">
	    <li>
		    <p><a name=3D"problem2"></a>The Atlanta Braves are having a walk-on t=
ryout camp for=20
		    baseball players. Thirty players show up at camp, but the coaches can=
 choose=20
		    only four. How many ways can four players be chosen from the 30 that =
have shown=20
		    up?</p>
		    <p><b>Solution:</b></p>
		    <p>The solution to this problem involves counting the number of combi=
nations of 30=20
		    players, taken 4 at a time. The number of combinations of <i>n</i> di=
stinct=20
		    objects, taken <i>r</i> at a time is:</p>
		    <p style=3D"text-align:center;">
			    <sub>n</sub>C<sub>r</sub> =3D n! / r! (n - r)!
			    <br>
			    <sub>30</sub>C<sub>4</sub> =3D 30! / 4!(30 - 4)! =3D 30! / 4! 26! =
=3D 27,405
		    </p>
		    <p>Thus, 27,405 different groupings of 4 players are possible.  To so=
lve=20
		    this problem using the=20
		    <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/online-calculator/combinations-permut=
ations#Calculator">Combination and Permutation Calculator</a>, do the follo=
wing:</p>
	        <ul>
	            <li>Enter "4" for "Subset size".</li>
	            <li>Enter "30" for "Set size".</li>
	            <li>Click the "Calculate" button.</li>
	        </ul>
	        <p>The answer, 27,405, is displayed in the "Combinations" textbox,=
 as shown below.</p>
	    </li>
    </ol>
